  "title": "Duration of treatment",
  "abstract": "So far, the epidemiology, prevention, diagnosis and treatment of deep vein thrombosis (DVT) have been addressed. This chapter will discuss how long patients with DVT should be treated. It will first present a conceptual framework about the duration of anticoagulation therapy in patients with DVT. It will then address the minimum duration of anticoagulation that applies to most patients and the factors to consider when deciding on extending anticoagulation beyond this minimum period. It will then review recommendations from three major guideline organizations. It will end by discussing the influence of sex and post-treatment D-dimer levels on extended therapy decision, and the use of extended antiplatelet therapy.",
